                            <comment id="12617120" author="koji" created="Sat, 26 Jul 2008 04:27:48 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;For backward compatibility, the patch supports both formats:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;@params&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;:highlighting&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;:max_snippets&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
      :highlighting =&amp;gt; {
        :max_snippets =&amp;gt; 3
      }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;@params&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;:highlighting&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;:max_snippets&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
      :highlighting =&amp;gt; {
        :max_snippets =&amp;gt; {
          :&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;default&lt;/span&gt;=&amp;gt;2,:fields=&amp;gt;{&apos;author&apos;=&amp;gt;3}
        }
      }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12617138" author="ehatcher" created="Sat, 26 Jul 2008 09:40:02 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Probably no need to worry about back compatibility too much with solr-ruby and the max_snippets stuff, since it is new since Solr 1.2.   But +1 in general.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
